{"brand_id": "lisraya", "doc_ref": "content_pattern_rules[1]", "end": 600, "heading_path": ["Typography Hierarchy (fonts, weights, cases)"], "kind": "list_item", "ordinal": 8, "schema_version": "2.0", "start": 524, "text": "- Available Nunito Sans weights: Light, Regular, SemiBold, Bold, ExtraBold.\n", "unit_id": "u_content_pattern_rules_1_0008"}
{"brand_id": "lisraya", "doc_ref": "content_pattern_rules[1]", "end": 642, "heading_path": ["Typography Hierarchy (fonts, weights, cases)"], "kind": "list_item", "ordinal": 9, "schema_version": "2.0", "start": 600, "text": "- Available Aptos weights: Regular, Bold.\n", "unit_id": "u_content_pattern_rules_1_0009"}
{"brand_id": "lisraya", "doc_ref": "content_pattern_rules[1]", "end": 919, "heading_path": ["Typography Hierarchy (fonts, weights, cases)"], "kind": "list_item", "ordinal": 10, "schema_version": "2.0", "start": 642, "text": "- **[GENERAL] Email font stack (CSS):** `'Nunito Sans', Verdana, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif`. Nunito Sans must be loaded via `@font-face`/Google Fonts link where the client supports it; the stack guarantees graceful fallback in Outlook and other clients that strip webfonts.\n", "unit_id": "u_content_pattern_rules_1_0010"}
{"brand_id": "lisraya", "doc_ref": "content_pattern_rules[1]", "end": 972, "heading_path": ["Typography Hierarchy (fonts, weights, cases)"], "kind": "list_item", "ordinal": 11, "schema_version": "2.0", "start": 919, "text": "- **[GENERAL] Email type scale (px / line-height):**\n", "unit_id": "u_content_pattern_rules_1_0011"}
{"brand_id": "lisraya", "doc_ref": "content_pattern_rules[1]", "end": 1055, "heading_path": ["Typography Hierarchy (fonts, weights, cases)"], "kind": "list_item", "ordinal": 12, "schema_version": "2.0", "start": 972, "text": "  - H1 (section hero headline): 28px / 36px (\u2248130%), Nunito Sans ExtraBold or Bold\n", "unit_id": "u_content_pattern_rules_1_0012"}
{"brand_id": "lisraya", "doc_ref": "content_pattern_rules[1]", "end": 1119, "heading_path": ["Typography Hierarchy (fonts, weights, cases)"], "kind": "list_item", "ordinal": 13, "schema_version": "2.0", "start": 1055, "text": "  - H2 (section heading): 22px / 30px (\u2248136%), Nunito Sans Bold\n", "unit_id": "u_content_pattern_rules_1_0013"}
{"brand_id": "lisraya", "doc_ref": "content_pattern_rules[1]", "end": 1187, "heading_path": ["Typography Hierarchy (fonts, weights, cases)"], "kind": "list_item", "ordinal": 14, "schema_version": "2.0", "start": 1119, "text": "  - H3 (subhead): 18px / 26px (\u2248144%), Nunito Sans Bold or SemiBold\n", "unit_id": "u_content_pattern_rules_1_0014"}
{"brand_id": "lisraya", "doc_ref": "content_pattern_rules[1]", "end": 1313, "heading_path": ["Typography Hierarchy (fonts, weights, cases)"], "kind": "list_item", "ordinal": 15, "schema_version": "2.0", "start": 1187, "text": "  - Body: 16px / 24px (150%), Nunito Sans Regular \u2014 **16px is the brand-mandated minimum for body copy (\"bigger is better\")**\n", "unit_id": "u_content_pattern_rules_1_0015"}
{"brand_id": "lisraya", "doc_ref": "content_pattern_rules[1]", "end": 1427, "heading_path": ["Typography Hierarchy (fonts, weights, cases)"], "kind": "list_item", "ordinal": 16, "schema_version": "2.0", "start": 1313, "text": "  - Secondary/supporting body: 14px / 21px (150%), Nunito Sans Regular \u2014 use sparingly, never for primary content\n", "unit_id": "u_content_pattern_rules_1_0016"}
{"brand_id": "lisraya", "doc_ref": "content_pattern_rules[1]", "end": 1571, "heading_path": ["Typography Hierarchy (fonts, weights, cases)"], "kind": "list_item", "ordinal": 17, "schema_version": "2.0", "start": 1427, "text": "  - Footnote/reference text within a section: 12px / 18px (150%) \u2014 must be \"noticeably smaller\" than primary data and clearly separated from it\n", "unit_id": "u_content_pattern_rules_1_0017"}
{"brand_id": "lisraya", "doc_ref": "content_pattern_rules[1]", "end": 1657, "heading_path": ["Typography Hierarchy (fonts, weights, cases)"], "kind": "list_item", "ordinal": 18, "schema_version": "2.0", "start": 1571, "text": "  - Never set running text below 12px. (ISI sizing is owned by the locked component.)\n", "unit_id": "u_content_pattern_rules_1_0018"}
{"brand_id": "lisraya", "doc_ref": "content_pattern_rules[1]", "end": 1832, "heading_path": ["Typography Hierarchy (fonts, weights, cases)"], "kind": "list_item", "ordinal": 19, "schema_version": "2.0", "start": 1657, "text": "- **Line height: minimum 150% for all body copy** (brand accessibility rule). **For light text on dark backgrounds, increase further** \u2014 [GENERAL] use 160% (e.g., 16px/26px).\n", "unit_id": "u_content_pattern_rules_1_0019"}
{"brand_id": "lisraya", "doc_ref": "content_pattern_rules[1]", "end": 2028, "heading_path": ["Typography Hierarchy (fonts, weights, cases)"], "kind": "list_item", "ordinal": 20, "schema_version": "2.0", "start": 1832, "text": "- Use a clear **type scale / visual hierarchy** so the reader knows what to read first, next, last. Never use two adjacent text blocks at the same size+weight to signal different hierarchy levels.", "unit_id": "u_content_pattern_rules_1_0020"}
